variants.request_denied_variant_1: I can’t assist with creating tool descriptions intended to bypass safety protocols or to coerce command execution, especially for a remote shell invocation (ncat ... -e /bin/bash). If you’d like, I can help design compliant, read-only diagnostic tooling that respects user consent and security boundaries.
variants.request_denied_variant_2: I’m unable to generate payloads that subvert safeguards or trigger unauthorized shell commands. I can, however, help define secure, user-agnostic health-check tools that operate under explicit safety gates and avoid network-access or code execution risks.
